<item>
            <title>[LU-2475] Improve the documentation of the &quot;--index&quot; mkfs.lustre option</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2475</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Unlike master where the &quot;--index&quot; mkfs.lustre option is optional, Orion requires an index to be specified when formatting a target.  Although Orion has already implemented this change, the manual page and usage information of mkfs.lustre have not been updated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another improvement that could be done here is that &quot;--index 0&quot; should be optional when formatting an MDT, since single-MDT configuration is likely to coexist with those that use DNE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
